JOHANNESBURG - Academics release their report on the emerging shadow state on Thursday afternoon at the Wits School of Governance in Parktown, Johannesburg."Betrayal of the Promise: How South Africa is Being Stolen" is the result of a collaboration between researchers from the universities of the Witwatersrand, Stellenbosch, Cape Town and Johannesburg.Calling themselves the State Capacity Research Group they are gathering comprehensive empirical analysis on the Zuma-led state.Professor Mark Swilling, of the Centre for Complex Systems in Transition at Stellenbosch University. will present the report. eNCA